  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": " Besu currently uses `contractSizeLimit` to specify the same thing \r\n\r\nTo increase EEA compliance, update Besu to use `maxCodeSize` as per the EEA spec.  \r\n\r\nBackwards compatibility needs to be consider and if a breaking change, will need to be made in a minor (eg, 1.5) or major release and clearly communicated in the release notes. \r\n\r\nTo solve backwards compatibility, @chaals has suggested that `maxCodeSize` should override `contractSizeLimit`. Otherwise, can use the `contractSizeLimit` value. ",
